{{Lunisolar November}} '''November 24''' is the 12th day of the month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)}}, the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar}}. Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜}}, and the day is designated as {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅}}.
== Events == * In the 1st year of the Kantoku era ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} 1044, December 16) – The era name was changed from Chōkyū to Kantoku.
== Births == * In the 8th year of the Kansei era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} 1796, December 22) – Torii Yōzō, a military retainer, was born (died 1873). * In the 1st year of the Meiji era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} 1869, January 6) – Takano Bōtarō, a labor movement activist, was born (died 1904).
== Deaths == * In the 1st year of the Bunroku era ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} 1592, December 27) – Kōsa, a Jōdo Shinshū monk who led a revolt against Oda Nobunaga, died (born 1543).
